    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI've grown used to using `\\v` in my search patterns. The problem is of course, that I'm either forced to awkwardly type them out each time or deal with unwieldy mappings.\n\nFor example mapping `:s` to `:s/\\v` is great until you want to run some other command starting with `s` (like `:source`) or when you want to use the `s//replacement` shortcut.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI propose a `'verymagic'` option similar to `'magic'`.\n\nThe obvious issue is of course conflict with existing plugins and runtime scripts. That can either be left for the user to deal with via autocommands (`CmdlineEnter, CmdlineLeave`) or the option could automatically only apply for searches invoked interactively.\n\nPersonally I would prefer the latter option, as it's hard to imagine a legitimate usecase for an option which breaks virtually all existing plugins if applied in non-interactive contexts.\n\nThe benefit could potentially be quite large, especially for new-ish users unaware of `\\v`. Default regexes are quite unwieldy as they require a lot of escaping. In time I would welcome this as an on-by-default option even.\n\nThe handling of \"interactive only\" would probably be quite tricky though, especially considering user commands defined in plugins and such.",
