            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "What is the expected behavior if 'verymagic' is set but 'magic' is NOT set? And how does `\\m` and `\\v` behave in each permutation? Super confusing for users and plugin authors.\n\nI'm surprised 'magic' isn't deprecated, we should have done that long ago. Introducing 'verymagic' makes even less sense.\n\n\n\n> For example mapping `:s` to `:s/\\v` is great until you want to run some other command starting with `s` (like `:source`) or when you want to use the `s//replacement` shortcut.\n\nWe need to think about a general approach for this, not another random flag. One idea is to introduce a new kind of abbreviation (there are currently three \"kinds\" described at `:help abbreviation`), which only activates if it is the *command* part of an *interactive* cmdline input. That solves this problem and others.\n\nMeanwhile, you can get pretty close to the ideal via `nvim_parse_cmd`, which allows a `CmdlineChanged` event-handler to correctly replace the relevant part of cmdline input.",
